2026-03-28  Ryan Musante

	Tagged as v1.0

	* retroarch.cfg: Initial drop-in configuration
	  - Target: Apple TV 4K 3rd Gen (2022), A15 Bionic, 128 GB
	  - Software: RetroArch v1.22.x (App Store), tvOS 18+
	  - All keys verified against RetroArch source (configuration.c)
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 1 — Menu (XMB driver)
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 2 — Video
	  - Metal driver, V-Sync, integer scaling, no bilinear filtering
	  - Shaders enabled globally, per-core disable via overrides
	  - Max swapchain images = 2 (verify on Metal)
	  - Aspect ratio index 22 (Core Provided)
	  - Threaded video intentionally omitted (crash #14978)
	  - Hard GPU sync intentionally omitted (no ARB_sync on Metal)
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 3 — Audio (48 ms latency default)
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 4 — Latency
	  - Preemptive frames enabled, 1 frame default
	  - Automatic frame delay enabled
	  - Late input polling (type 2)
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 5 — Hotkeys
	  - L3+R3 menu toggle (combo index 2)
	  - Additional hotkeys documented as GUI-only
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 6 — Directories
	  - File browser, BIOS, saves, states under Config/
	  - ":"  prefix for tvOS app content root
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 7 — Cloud Sync (iCloud CloudKit backend)
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 8 — Save management
	  - Sort by core name, not content directory
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 9 — Rewind (disabled globally)
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 10 — CRT shader reference table
	  - 9 recommended presets with GPU load ratings
	  - Per-core shader assignments
	  - GPU-intensive presets listed as avoid
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 11 — BIOS file placement reference
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 12 — Recommended cores per system
	  - Tier 1/2/3 classification with rationale
	  - PPSSPP GL workaround for Metal/Vulkan crash (#18050)
	  - Azahar (3DS) experimental status noted
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 13 — Folder structure reference
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 14 — Post-install checklist (22 items)
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 15 — Per-core override reference
	  - 12 cores with specific override recommendations
	  - GitHub issue references for N64 bugs (#18300, #14201)
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 16 — Known issues table (10 entries)
	* retroarch.cfg: Section 17 — 4th Gen (2026) projected hardware notes
	  - A17 Pro spec comparison
	  - Per-setting impact analysis
	  - Per-core override change projections
	  - Connectivity and storage improvements
	  - Constraints that do not change
	* retroarch-apple-tv-setup-guide.pdf: Source document
	  - 16 pages, 18 sections
	  - Verified against RetroArch source, Libretro docs, GitHub issues
